    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Honest little car that\u2019s not winning any beauty contests, but it\u2019s a great budget-friendly option for someone who wants simple, affordable wheels or a solid project to tinker with. It has the kind of character you\u2019d expect from an older used car, and for the money it offers a lot of practical value. If you\u2019re after cheap transportation or something to fix up your way, this one is definitely worth a look.",
      "price": 6950.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 28
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Solid, no-frills used car with dependable core mechanicals and plenty of life left for the next owner. Engine starts up willingly, transmission pulls through the gears as it should, and the chassis feels planted enough to serve as a practical commuter, backup vehicle, or entry-level project. It shows its age cosmetically and is best described as an honest driver rather than a showpiece, but for someone who values usable transportation and straightforward serviceability, there is real value here. A great opportunity to get into an affordable car with proven basics at a sensible price.",
      "price": 5950.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
